## Reflection on Causality

The Nerevarine Prophecy illustrates a fundamental paradox in Tamriel: do prophecies cause events, or do events cause prophecies? Azura foretold Nerevar's return because the Tribunal had betrayed — but the Tribunal was punished because the prophecy existed. The Emperor sent the prisoner because he knew the prophecy — but the prophecy was fulfilled because the Emperor sent the prisoner.

What is certain is that the causal chain initiated by the betrayal of 1E 700 did not truly end until the Red Year of 4E 5 — more than three thousand years of cascading consequences, triggered by a single act of perjury at the summit of Red Mountain.
